📁 VIDEO BACKUP SCRIPT FOR TERMUX  

This Python script copies all video files from one folder to another in Termux.  

🚀 INSTALLATION & USAGE  

1. Open Termux  
2. Install Python:  
   pkg install python  
3. Create a folder for the project:  
   mkdir VideoBackup && cd VideoBackup  
4. Add a main file named "copy_videos.py"  
5. Write the script inside "copy_videos.py"  
6. Save and exit  
7. Run the program with:  
   python copy_videos.py  

🛠 HOW IT WORKS  
✔️ Copies all videos from `/sdcard/Videos` to `/sdcard/Backup_Videos`  
✔️ Automatically creates the destination folder if it doesn't exist  
✔️ Supports `.mp4`, `.avi`, `.mkv`, `.mov`, `.flv` formats  

🎉 EXAMPLE OUTPUT  
✅ Copied: my_video.mp4  
✅ Copied: movie.avi  
🎉 Copy completed!  

